    "A backward propagation technique called LRP gives relevance scores to a model's input features based on how much they contribute to the output.",
    "The most crucial neurons for the prediction are then identified through the model layers using the relevance scores.",
    "Additionally, LRP deals with the shortcomings of shattered gradients in gradient methods (Grad-CAM) and perturbation methods (occlusion maps) 69.",
    "We utilized Google Colab and PyTorch for simulation and obtaining results.",
    "Google Colab furnished the necessary computational resources, while PyTorch was an efficient framework for constructing and training DL models."
